<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-04-11T21:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-04-11T21:00:00-05:00" n="351" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d351">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">123 Merchant, Livingston T.: Telegram</note>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Taipei</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Edgar</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                        </hi>
                    </head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Taipei</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-04-12T10:00:00+08:00">April 12,
                                1949—10 a. m.</date>
                            <lb/> [Received April 12—3:45 a. m.]</dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>114. From Merchant. Strongly recommend Paul Parker and I be immediately
                        recalled consultation Washington. If recommendation <pb facs="0325" n="315" xml:id="pg_315"/> Taipei’s 113, April 12 accepted, no immediate action
                        required here and combined full understanding problems essential for
                        successful operation. Confident Treasury would cooperate for Parker’s return
                        with me. [Merchant.]</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Edgar</hi>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>